The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, Dec. 15: The government will invite expressions of interest from financial institutions for selling a part of its remaining stake in Maruti Udyog next week. ?Expressions of interest from public sector financial institutions for 8 per cent of the government?s 18.28 per cent stake in Maruti will be invited next week,? sources said. Advisers to the sale ? SBI Capital Markets and Kotak Mahindra ? have reportedly arrived at the floor price of Maruti shares keeping the market price as a benchmark.

 Mumbai, Dec. 15: Reliance Industries Ltd today told the National Stock Exchange that Bhumika Trading Pvt Ltd has proposed to acquire 4.94 crore shares in the company.

 New Delhi, Dec 15: The civil aviation ministry has received several complaints on the bidding process for modernising Delhi and Mumbai airports. It has forwarded them to appropriate authorities for a review, said civil aviation minister Praful Patel.

 New Delhi, Dec. 15: The government today introduced a bill in the Lok Sabha to provide operational flexibility and smooth functioning of the Central Sales Tax Appellate Authority and provide more time to traders to file appeals.

 New Delhi, Dec. 15: The Centre?s tax collections increased more than 19 per cent to Rs 1,90,879 crore during April to November, 2005. Direct taxes grew 25 per cent to Rs 71,237 crore during the period from Rs 56,798 crore a year ago.




